        "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\noh. that's true. no sli dependency anymore. @ravi: can be removed everywhere",
        "patchset_number": 5
      },
      {
        "id": "3caef230ba8bf44c7f49b2f605c6b2e4e3f42f79",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 87,
          "name": "Dan Timoney",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "dtimoney@att.com",
          "username": "djtimoney"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2021-07-27 13:34:12.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 5: Code-Review-1\n\n(1 comment)\n\n2 general comments:\n1) Instead of defining your own property for versions of CCSDK dependencies (e.g. sli.version), please use the properties defined in the parent poms (e.g. ccsdk.sli.version) for project uniformity.\n2) I won't insist on this, but I strongly suggest you avoid using \"mariadb\" in your class and package names in favor of something more generic like 'sql'. Otherwise some developers could be misled into thinking this code has a hard dependency on MariaDB as a backend (which it doesn't seem to, since the mariadb JDBC client is compatible with MySQL as well). Also, using more generic names now could save refactoring work later if someone wanted to add support for another relational database like H2 or postgres.",
        "patchset_number": 5
      },
